  "texts": [
    "The initial density grid estimation is inspected and cleaned using the interactive eraser function described in Section 4.1.",
    "Users can manually remove regions with cloudy prediction errors or low render quality.",
    "The edited density grid and the binary bitmask of the density grid are stored in the NeRF model for reuse.",
    "When reloading the cleaned NeRF model, our framework automatically checks the saved bitmask, so that the erroneous network prediction that has already been removed will no longer be sampled and rendered.",
    "The user could manually align the cleaned NeRF model with the CAD model using the NeRF object manipulation and crop box editing functions described in Section 4.1."
  ],
